# ==========================================
# PRIVATE SCHOOL WEBSITE PROJECT RULES
# Stack: Astro (v4+), Sanity CMS (v3+), Tailwind CSS
# Environment: Windows 11 (PowerShell), Cloudflare Pages
# ==========================================

# 1. CORE ARCHITECTURE & DATA FLOW
- This website is a flat, static build hosted on Cloudflare Pages. 
- All dynamic data (Homepage blocks, PDFs, alerts) must be fetched at build-time using `@astrojs/sanity` and GROQ queries.
- Do not add client-side database connections or run-time admin login pages to the public frontend website.
- Use Sanity singletons for fixed pages (Home, Admissions) and document arrays/collections for repeating lists (Staff, Announcements).
- Optimize images using the `@sanity/image-url` helper to dynamically crop and compress admin-uploaded photos at build-time.

# 2. FILE PATHS & TERMINAL RULES (WINDOWS NATIVE)
- Every single terminal or CLI command provided must be 100% valid, native Windows PowerShell (pwsh) syntax.
- Use explicit backslashes (\) for all Windows file system directories and paths.
- Avoid Linux-specific utilities like `mkdir -p` or `touch`. Use `New-Item` or explicit instructions for creating files.
- When generating string commands in terminal scripts, ensure proper double-quote wrapping compatible with PowerShell.

# 3. FRONTEND & STYLING SPECIFICATIONS
- Use modern Astro component architecture (`.astro` files). Separate backend script frontmatter (between `---`) from semantic HTML template markups.
- Style exclusively with utility-first Tailwind CSS classes. No inline styles or external `.css` files unless absolutely mandatory.
- All page layouts and blocks must be meticulously crafted with a mobile-first responsive grid. School parents will view this site heavily on smartphones.
- Build clean component primitives (e.g., `Header.astro`, `Footer.astro`, `AlertBanner.astro`) to eliminate code duplication across pages.
- Meticulously implement touch-friendly targets (minimum 48x48px) for all phone interaction links.
- Explicitly integrate the '@sanity/image-url' builder to serve compressed, web-optimized webp image sizes for mobile networks.
- Enforce standard mobile-native web protocols including 'tel:' for phone connections and 'mailto:' for school admin emails.
- Build clean, fluid-responsive components that naturally transition between desktop grids and single-column mobile layouts.

# 4. CODE DELIVERABLES EXPECTATION
- Provide complete, copy-pasteable files rather than vague code fragments.
- Clearly state the exact Windows path location where the file belongs at the very top of your response.

1. Global Settings (Managed Once)These are items that appear everywhere on the site.Sanity Blocks: School Phone Number, Admin Email Address, Alerts Banner (e.g., "Snow Day Close!").Astro Layout: Astro takes these fields and automatically updates your site-wide header and footer.
